  "notes": "Cantabrian Spanish (Montañés). Northern conservative dialect with Asturleonese substrate. Apico-alveolar [s̺] (northern type), distinción (lleísmo/yeísmo distinction) preserved. Partial yeísmo: /ʎ/ preserved in older speakers, merged with /j/ in younger speakers. Asturian substrate features include unstressed vowel raising (e→i, o→u) and neutralization of ser/estar. Transitional between Castilian and Asturian; some Leonese metaphony traces in western areas.",
